</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="356" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[685,1172,193,719]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,966,353,374]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Geographic Distribution.</emphasis>
We examined specimens from Cochise, Gila, Graham, and Pima Counties in 
<collectingRegion box="[807,886,406,427]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Arizona</collectingRegion>
. Although we have not seen specimens, this species is also reported from 
<collectingRegion country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">California</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wilcox, J. A." box="[762,891,459,480]" journalOrPublisher="New York State Museum and Science Service Bulletin" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" pagination="1 - 226" part="400" refId="ref12891" refString="Wilcox, J. A. 1965. A synopsis of the North American Galerucinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). New York State Museum and Science Service Bulletin 400: 1 - 226." title="A synopsis of the North American Galerucinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)" type="journal article" year="1965">Wilcox 1965</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="356" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[685,1172,193,719]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,953,486,507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Temporal Distribution.</emphasis>
We eamined adults collected from April to June.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[685,1172,193,719]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,899,539,560]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Plant Associations.</emphasis>
This species is reported from 
<taxonomicName box="[685,750,565,586]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Nolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[685,750,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Nolina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the flowers of a yellow composite (
<taxonomicName box="[692,798,592,613]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Wilcox, J. A." box="[818,946,592,613]" journalOrPublisher="New York State Museum and Science Service Bulletin" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" pagination="1 - 226" part="400" refId="ref12891" refString="Wilcox, J. A. 1965. A synopsis of the North American Galerucinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). New York State Museum and Science Service Bulletin 400: 1 - 226." title="A synopsis of the North American Galerucinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)" type="journal article" year="1965">Wilcox 1965</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, S. M. &amp; D. G. LeDoux &amp; T. N. Seeno &amp; E. G. Riley &amp; A. J. Gilbert &amp; J. M. Sullivan" box="[958,1127,592,613]" journalOrPublisher="The Coleopterists Society Special Publication" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" pagination="1 - 476" part="2" refId="ref11983" refString="Clark, S. M., D. G. LeDoux, T. N. Seeno, E. G. Riley, A. J. Gilbert, and J. M. Sullivan. 2004. Host plants of leaf beetle species occurring in the United States and Canada (Coleoptera: Megalopodidae, Orsodacnidae, Chrysomelidae, excluding Bruchinae). The Coleopterists Society Special Publication 2: 1 - 476." title="Host plants of leaf beetle species occurring in the United States and Canada (Coleoptera: Megalopodidae, Orsodacnidae, Chrysomelidae, excluding Bruchinae)" type="journal article" year="2004">
Clark 
<emphasis box="[1018,1068,592,613]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
). Included in the material we examined, there are specimens labeled as from the flowers of 
<taxonomicName box="[1091,1156,645,666]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Nolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1091,1156,645,666]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Nolina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="356" type="discussion">
